With the same coeffecient of expansion, the percentage expansion is the same 
for both parts. But since the hub has a  _slightly_  larger diameter than 
the race, the physical incresae in diameter is slightly greater for the the 
larger part, so you do get some loosening.

1% of 1.001 is greater than 1% of 1.000

I've used 300-400 degrees F and it seems to make the difference for my hubs. 
Still gotta pound the **** out of them though.

